Well for a bunch of parallel arrays you aren&#x27;t really moving big blocks.  Consider this:<p><pre><code>  struct City {
    char *name;
    int   popstrat[5];
    float bounds[2];
  };
</code></pre>
A a memcpy on struct City would take care of eight distinct values, whereas a copy operation on a parallel arrays version would take at least three separate memcpy calls (maybe eight if naively implemented).<p>I certainly agree with you on the weight given to O notation though.
